gomodel:SYNGO_1709  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Neurabin-I is a known actin-binding protein (see Additional literature and others).\nFig.1: GFP-NrbI Is Concentrated in Dendritic Spines\nFig.2: Spine Localization of GFP-NrbI Requires the Intact Actin Cytoskeleton\n\nTogether this shows that in the postsynapse neurabin is localized to the actin cytoskeleton (hippocampal neurons).. Experimental description: - Rat neurons are used: \"Hippocampal slices were prepared from P6 or P7 rats as described\"\n- Species of overexpressed Neurabin 1 traced back to PMID:12052877 \"...were generated by PCR with full-length rat NrbI cDNA as template \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-02" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1709" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

